com.orbitz.monitoring.api.monitor
Class AttributeMap

java.lang.Object
  com.orbitz.monitoring.api.monitor.AttributeMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
CompositeAttributeMap
public class AttributeMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

A map-like class that can be used to hold attributes for a Monitor. This class requires that keys are strings. Also, it has methods for getting and setting primitives as the values of those attributes. This map does not support null values. Values set to null are removed from the the map.

internalSetAttribute

protected AttributeHolder internalSetAttribute(java.lang.String key,
                                               java.lang.Object value)
Puts an attribute into the map.
  • If the key does not exist, the new value is put.
  • If the key exists, but the related AttributeHolder is locked ( AttributeHolder.isLocked()), nothing happens
  • If the key exists and the related AttributeHolder is not locked ( AttributeHolder.isLocked()), the new value is put and the settings of the existing AttributeHolder, such as AttributeHolder.isSerializable() and CompositeAttributeHolder.isInheritable(), are copied to the new holder.

Parameters:
key - the key of the value to put
value - the value to put
Returns:
if the value was put, the new AttributeHolder. Otherwise, the the AttributeHolder of value that already existed for the specified key.

set

public AttributeHolder set(java.lang.String key,
                           boolean value)
Sets a value. See internalSetAttribute(String, Object) for information about whether the value will be set and how it will be set.

Parameters:
key - the key that identifies the value
value - the value to set
Returns:
if the new value was put into the map, the AttributeHolder created to hold it. If the new value was not put, the AttributeHolder for the value that already existed in the map.

setAllAttributeHolders

public void setAllAttributeHolders(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> attributeHolders)
Sets zero or more attribute holders from a collection. If an entry value is an AttributeHolder, it is cloned and its clone is put in this map. If it is not an AttributeHolder, it is placed in a new attribute holder and put in this map.

Parameters:
attributeHolders - a map of string keys to their holders or not holders. Really, anything.
